     2→//! src/module_8.rs
     3→//!
     4→//! LedgerLink Nexus – Module 8
     5→//!
     6→//! This module brings together three horizontal concerns required by
     7→//! high-volume endpoints such as `GET /v1/ledger-entries`:
     8→//!     1. Robust, cursor-based pagination helpers
     9→//!     2. Response-caching via Redis (or an in-memory fallback for tests)
    10→//!     3. Command/Query service façade that coordinates repository access,
    11→//!        validation, tracing and cache hydration.
    12→//!
    13→//! The implementation is self-contained in a single file for the purpose of
    14→//! the example, but in the production code-base every sub-module would live
    15→//! in its own file and be wired together using dependency-injection.
    16→//!
    17→//! The public items exposed here are intended to be consumed by the HTTP
    18→//! or GraphQL layers, hiding all infrastructure details behind clean,
    19→//! async traits.
    20→//!
    21→//! -------------------------------------------------------------------------
    22→
    23→#![allow(dead_code)]
