     2→//! src/module_71.rs
     3→//!
     4→//! Cash-Flow Forecast query service with optional Redis-backed response
     5→//! caching, pagination helpers and domain-driven abstractions.
     6→//!
     7→//! This module is completely self-contained yet showcases the LedgerLink
     8→//! Nexus architecture principles:
     9→//!   • Clean separation between View (DTO)  ➜  View-Model (validated
    10→//!     transport structs)  ➜  Domain Models / Repository  ➜  Service.
    11→//!   • Transparent response-caching with Redis using a typed cache key.
    12→//!   • Structured error handling with `thiserror` and `tracing`.
    13→//!   • Feature-gated compile options (`response_caching`) for optional
    14→//!     dependencies, keeping binary size and attack-surface minimal.
    15→//!
    16→//! Down-stream HTTP/GraphQL handlers can simply call
    17→//! `CashFlowForecastService::get_forecast(..)` and receive a fully
    18→//! validated, paginated & (optionally) cached payload ready to be
    19→//! serialized by the transport layer.
