     2→//! src/module_20.rs
     3→//!
     4→//! LedgerLink Nexus – Ledger Entry Query Module (with Pagination & Redis Caching)
     5→//!
     6→//! This module lives in the “View-Model / Service” layer of the micro-service. It is responsible
     7→//! for fetching paginated ledger entries for a given tenant, while transparently leveraging a
     8→//! Redis cache to reduce pressure on Postgres for hot queries.
     9→//!
    10→//! Architectural notes
    11→//! -------------------
    12→//! • View <- ViewModel (DTO + metadata) <- Service <- Repository  (MVVM inspired)
    13→//! • Command/Query separation is respected; this module is *read-only* (query).
    14→//! • Error envelopes are unified and converted higher up in the middleware-stack.
    15→//!
    16→//! Crate features used
    17→//! -------------------
    18→//! async-trait, serde, thiserror, chrono, uuid, rust_decimal, redis (aio), tokio
    19→//! ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
    20→
    21→use std::sync::Arc;
    22→use std::time::Duration;
    23→
