     2→//! LedgerLink Nexus – Response Caching Middleware
     3→//!
     4→//! This module provides an Actix-Web compatible middleware that transparently
     5→//! caches successful GET / HEAD responses in Redis.  The middleware
     6→//! understands the multi-tenant nature of the platform (every key is
     7→//! automatically prefixed with the tenant id) and cooperates with the
     8→//! pagination layer by using the full query string in the cache key.
     9→//!
    10→//! Recommended usage (inside `main.rs` or the app factory):
    11→//! ```no_run
    12→//! use ledgerlink_nexus::middleware::{response_cache, response_cache::ResponseCache};
    13→//!
    14→//! fn app(redis: deadpool_redis::Pool) -> App {
    15→//!     App::new()
    16→//!         .wrap(ResponseCache::new(redis, response_cache::Config::default()))
    17→//!         // … more middleware & routes
    18→//! }
    19→//! ```
    20→//! The middleware is production-ready and follows the Repository / Service
    21→//! architecture mandated by LedgerLink Nexus. All error variants are mapped
    22→//! to structured problem details envelopes before being returned to the
    23→//! caller.
    24→
    25→#![deny(clippy::all)]
    26→#![deny(clippy::pedantic)]
    27→#![allow(clippy::module_name_repetitions)] // middlware naming is explicit
